The paper deals with designing an online algorithm for a network design problem, which involves graph theory and optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely sub-category. The paper also involves the design of a novel approach for solving mixed packing/covering integer programs, which falls under the scope of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The problem of designing online algorithms for network design problems is also relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
